name: Event/Component Category (V1)
description: The main category or component an Interaction belongs to, e.g. "Suggested Search", "Filter", etc...

name: Event Action/Cause (V2)
description: What is causing an Event (e.g. a click on a suggested search result) - sometimes also simply used to further detail an Event (to remain aligned with GA)

name: Event Label (V3)
description: A readable description of an Event - sometimes also simply used to further detail an Event (to remain aligned with GA)

name: Event/Component Sub-Category1 (V4)
description: A variable to detail an interaction with a component. The meaning depends on the Component/Event Category.

name: Component Aspect 1 (V5)
description: A variable to detail an interaction with a component. The meaning depends on the Component/Event Category.

name: Component Aspect 2 (V6)
description: A variable to detail an interaction with a component. The meaning depends on the Component/Event Category.

name: Component ID (V7)
description: Allows to distinguish several instances of the same component on one page (e.g. several teaser boxes on the homepage)

name: Component Location (V8)
description: Location where an interaction with a component happened (e.g. footer, header etc.)

name: Component Inner Location (V9)
description: The location inside of a component where an interaction happened (e.g. the position of a teaser within a teaser grid component)

name: Net Promoter Score Raw (V10) - User
description: Net Promoter Score Raw

name: User Purchase History (V11)
description: Purchase History of a User (to identify Repeat Buyers)

name: Content Language (V12)
description: Language of the current Page's content (can be manually chosen by the user)

name: Internal Search - Clicked Result Position (V13)
description: The Position the internal Search Result had which was clicked

name: Internal Search Result Count (V14)
description: Number of Results in the Internal Search

name: Internal Search Term (V15)
description: Expires after purchase - linear allocation to show all search terms a user used until purchase happened

name: Page Title (V17)
description: The HTML Page Title (shortened to 100 chars)

name: Site Section (V18)
description: Site Section as eVar (to be able to use it in any report where V-Variables are needed) - available since 1/28/2016

name: Clean URL (V19)
description: URL cleaned from typical URL parameters like utm_source, gclid, j_con etc. as well as the hash (#...). For the entire URL, see Full URL (V20).

name: Full URL (V20) - debugging
description: Full Actual URL with all Query String Parameters, no lowercasing, and hash (#). Used for debugging mostly. For Reporting, use V19 - Clean URL

name: URL Pathname + Clean Query String (V24)
description: A copy of the PageName when = Pathname plus Query String cleaned from typical URL parameters like utm_source, gclid, j_con etc...

name: Clean URL Query String (V27)
description: The Query String cleaned from typical URL parameters like utm_source, gclid, j_con etc... For the entire query string, see Full URL Query String (V23).

name: Event:Path+Clean QueryStr (V28)
description: Shows the Event Type (Event Category/"P" for Pageview) plus Pathname+Query String for any Hit (Pageview or Event) and thus allows Pathing for Event and Pageview Hits

name: Event:Pathname (V29)
description: Shows the Event Type (Event Category/"P" for Pageview) plus Pathname for any Hit (Pageview or Event) and thus allows Pathing for Event and Pageview Hits.

name: Siroop ID (Unique Customer ID, ucid) (V30)
description:
Starting with resiroop (early 2018), this is the unique Customer Identifier
(used to be Report Suite ID until July 2017)

name: Device Viewport (V31)
description: Device Type, induced from the User's viewport (e.g. when I view a browser tab very small on a Desktop, the Device Viewport will be "mobile" anyway.

name: Weekday (V32)
description: Day of the Week from Sunday to Saturday (1=Sunday, 7=Saturday). Available since 1/29/2016

name: Date (YYYYMMDD) (V33)
description: Full Date in format YYYMMDD - available since April 22, 2016

name: Registered User (User) (V34)
description: y = User with this device ID Cookie has registered in the past (has had a Registered User ID Cookie at least once)

name: Client ID (V35) - formerly Device ID
description: The value of the Client ID Cookie (general User Cookie), earlier called "Device ID".

name: Reg. User ID (User) (V36)
description: The value of the Reg. User ID Cookie "siroid"

name: Login Status (Hit) (V37)
description: y = user was logged in during this hit, n = user was not logged in

name: Payment Type of Completed Order (V38)
description: Payment Type of an Order, tracked when order is completed only

name: Refund Reason (V39)
description: The reason why a transaction or a product were refunded (e.g. Cancellation or Refund)

name: Merchant as shown on site (V41-Merch)
description: The Merchant name that the user sees on the site (no White-Label Merchants)

name: Prod Name (V46-Merch)
description: Product Name (cut to the first 99 characters to avoid requests being cut off)

name: Prod Price during Hit (V47-Merch)
description:
New since Nov 2017: the price of a product during the current hit (e.g. the cart add, pdp view, cart view etc.)

earlier: The Variant String of the Product (-1, -2 etc.) was not used anymore after Prod Variants Go-Live (Oct 2016)

name: Prod Position (V48-Merch)
description: Position of a Product in a List

name: Prod Delivery (V49-Merch)
description: The delivery method chosen for a product

name: Cart Value (V50)
description: Value in the shopping cart (since 3/7/2016)

name: Prod Concrete ID (V51)
description: The ID of a fully configured product (e.g. iPhone 6S with 64GB)

name: Prod Group ID (V52-Merch)
description: The Group ID of the Group that a Product can belong to (e.g. all iPhone 6S in all colors belong to group "iPhone 6S")

name: Merchant ID (V53-Merch)
description: Merchant ID - available since Variants go live (mid-October 2016)

name: Product Display Context (V55-Merch)
description: Name of the Product Context (list name, cart, detail etc.) in which a Product was viewed or clicked

name: Prod Voucher Code: Descr (V56-Merch)
description: Product Voucher Code: Descr (Discount, "Coupon Code")

name: Prod In Stock (V57)
description:
Know if a product on PDP was out of stock or is low. Tracking starts 2016-12 (CC-131). 
Values:
>=5 : if 5 or more items available
<5 : if less than 5

name: Prod Ad Label (V58)
description: Product sales label (e.g. "Topsellers", "PriceDrop"). Tracking starts 2016-12 (CC-95)

name: ProductsUp Ad Label String (V59)
description: String of temporary Product Attributes as transmitted from ProductsUp via Data Layer Enrichment Extension in Tealium

name: User ZIP Code (V60)
description: User Zip Code. Is gathered in Checkout.

name: User Gender (V61)
description: User Gender. Is gathered in Checkout.

name: User Age (V62)
description: User Age. Is gathered in Checkout.

name: User Email (Encrypted) (V63)
description: Encrypted Email of user as gathered in checkout.

name: Cart ID (V64)
description: Persistent ID of a shopping cart

name: Mktg Touchpoint - last (V65)
description: The last Marketing Touchpoint

name: Mktg Touchpoint Path (V66)
description: Up to 8 Marketing Touchpoints in one string. The newest touchpoint is to the left.

name: Mkt Granular Touchpoint - last (V67)
description: The last Marketing Touchpoint in granular form. "Granular" means: AdWords Touchpoint plus AdW Campaign ID OR utm_campaign OR Hostname of Referrer for Organic Search/Referral:

name: Mkt Granular Touchpoint Path (V68)
description: Up to 6 granular Marketing Touchpoints in one string. The newest touchpoint is to the left. "Granular" means: AdWords Touchpoint plus AdW Campaign ID OR utm_campaign OR Hostname of Referrer for Organic Search/Referral:

name: Campaign Name (utm_campaign) (V69)
description: The decoded value of the utm_campaign parameter

name: Campaign ID (Linear Allocation) (V70)
description: The Campaign ID where each value is attributed to a Conversion Metric. Expires after Purchase. Active since 03/11/2016

name: AdWords Value Track Parameters (V71)
description: AdWords ValueTrack Parameters and Values (only non-empty parameters), e.g. "network=g&campaignid=398881463&adgroupid=25196398103&keyword=&matchtype=&adposition=1o1&adtype=pla&merchant_id=108201559&product_id=104165-4&feeditemid=&targetid=pla-178713697703"

name: Campaign Content (V72)
description: Campaign Content (like utm_content in Google Analytics)

name: Non-Google Paid Search Term (utm_term) (V73)
description: Non-Google (e.g. Bing)  Paid Search Term (utm_term) V73)

name: Product List Clicked Name (V75-Merch)
description: Name of the Product List in which a Product was clicked

name: Product Commission Level (V76)
description: shows the Commission Level per sold product in percent

name: PDP Attributes (V77)
description: Attributes of the PDP: mc:[count of merchants]#lp:[lowest price]

name: Email Job ID - ExactTarget (V80)
description: The email Job ID in ExactTarget (Salesforce Marketing Cloud)

name: depr. Feb 2018: Email Recipient ID - ExactTarget (V81)
description: Not used anymore since Feb 2018: The email Recipient ID in ExactTarget (Salesforce Marketing Cloud) - either siroid or encrypted email

name: Lifetime Devices Used (V82)
description: Devices used by the Visitor according to Visitor Stitching via Tealium Audience Stream

name: Lifetime Browsers Used (V83)
description: Browsers used by the Visitor according to Visitor Stitching via Tealium Audience Stream

name: User Lifetime Order Count (V84)
description: Counts how many lifetime orders a user has. Enriched via Audience Stream

name: Raw: Days Since Last Purchase (V85)
description: Counts days since last order via Audience Stream Enrichment

name: UTC Timestamp (V88)
description: UTC Timestamp  in Milliseconds (V88). JS generated. Example: "2018-02-08T16:34:24.660Z"

name: Tealium Session ID (V89)
description: The Tealium Session ID

name: Day-Hour-Minutes (V90)
description: Day-Hour-Minutes, e.g. 071504 (7th day of month, 15:04)

name: DFA Data Connector (V91)
description: Automatically populated with DFA Tracking Code by nightly import (DFA Data Connector).

name: DFA Data Connector View-Through Time Frame
Siroop Platform (V94)
description: beta, spryker, jobs or others

name: Session Hit Counter (V96)
description: Increments on every Hit of a Session

name: Session Pageview Counter (V97)
description: Increments on every Pageview of a Session

name: Tealium Version (V98) - discont. 5/29/17, now part of V99
Debug Information (V99)
description: contains, separated by pipe: Tealium Version|Tealium environment|Report Suite ID|LocalStorage Support|sync_run (has the utag.sync.js tag run successfully?)|DLExt Available|Random Visitor percentage

name: Siroop ID (Unique Customer ID, ucid) (V100) (copy of V30)
description: Starting with resiroop (early 2018), this is the unique Customer Identifier. Copied into a separate eVar to avoid potential problems of previous of old values of V30 persisting here
